yield: for 400g pork belly
ingredients:
  - item: pork belly
    mass: 400
    basis: true
    note: or spare rib strips, cubed
  - item: veg oil
    note: amount tbd during caramelising
  - item: sugar
    mass: 20
  - item: onion
    note: chopped
  - item: dark soy
    qty: 0.25
    unit: cup
  - item: light soy
    qty: 0.25
    unit: cup
  - item: shaoxing
    qty: 0.25
    unit: cup
  - item: water
    note: top up as needed
steps:
  - blanch pork belly cubes for a few mins and drain
  - add veg oil and sugar to a 160°C pan to melt and start caramelising (few mins)
  - add chopped onion and cook for a few mins until translucent
  - add pork
  - add dark soy, light soy, and shaoxing
  - top up with water
  - cover with lid and simmer for 1.5 hours, stirring every 15 mins to prevent burning
  - remove lid and cook down to thicken sauce
notes: |
  Jap variant:
  - Replace shaoxing with sake
  - Add 1/8 cup mirin
  - Drop soys to 1/8 cup each
  - Add a teaspoon/tbsp of miso
